### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### [E] TIMING ORACLE — both paths must take ≥ 100ms
###
### Measure response time shown by REST Client (bottom of response panel)
### or use: curl -o /dev/null -s -w "%{time_total}\n" <url>
###
### PASS:  Both E-1 and E-2 are ≥ 0.100s and within ~50ms of each other
### FAIL:  E-1 (INVALID) is ~0.001s and E-2 (ACTIVE) is ~0.015s
###        → timing oracle still open, MIN_RESPONSE_MS floor not working
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# [E-1] INVALID path — pure crypto, no DB (~1ms without fix, ≥100ms with fix)
GET {{BASE_URL}}{{SCAN_PATH}}/0000000000000000000000000000000000000000000
User-Agent: TimingTest/1.0
X-Forwarded-For: 192.0.2.50
Accept: application/json

###

# [E-2] ACTIVE path — crypto + DB + profile build (~15ms without fix, ≥100ms with fix)
GET {{BASE_URL}}{{SCAN_PATH}}/{{VALID_CODE}}
User-Agent: TimingTest/1.0
X-Forwarded-For: 192.0.2.51
Accept: application/json

###

# [E-3] REVOKED path — crypto + DB, no profile build
GET {{BASE_URL}}{{SCAN_PATH}}/{{REVOKED_CODE}}
User-Agent: TimingTest/1.0
X-Forwarded-For: 192.0.2.52
Accept: application/json


